                    <h2 class="panel-title">
                        <a id="accordion-1584725931219-stay-informed-but-avoid-excessive--exposure-to-news-about-covid-19" role="tab" data-toggle="collapse" data-parent="#bfc0e323-bf60-448a-99c6-83eda6778558" href="#accordion-content-1584725931219-stay-informed-but-avoid-excessive--exposure-to-news-about-covid-19" aria-controls="accordion-content-1584725931219-stay-informed-but-avoid-excessive--exposure-to-news-about-covid-19" aria-expanded="false">
                            Stay informed but avoid excessive  exposure to news about COVID-19
                        </a>
                    </h2>
                    
                </div>
                <!-- Accordion Body -->
                <div tabindex="0" id="accordion-content-1584725931219-stay-informed-but-avoid-excessive--exposure-to-news-about-covid-19" class="panel-collapse collapse" role="tabpanel" aria-labelledby="accordion-1584725931219-stay-informed-but-avoid-excessive--exposure-to-news-about-covid-19">
                    <div class="panel-body ">
                        <div class="1584725931219 stackparsys">










				
				<div class="resText parbase section">


























<div class="res-text richtextContent background-hidden" id="9576c8d6-8590-4cbd-b37a-cbd00fef130c" >

    <p>Use credible sources to receive information about the situation. Don't spend all your time focusing on the pandemic as continuous reading or listening to media coverage can unnecessarily intensify agitation, worry, and stress.</p> 
<p>Try…</p> 
<ul> 
 <li>Checking once a day for regular updates from official sources like Toronto Public Health, Health Canada, and CBC.</li> 
 <li>Avoid relying on social media for news - use those tools for connection, joy, and storytelling instead. news from social media</li> 
</ul>
    





</div>
<script>$(document).ready(function(){addCoursePopover("#9576c8d6-8590-4cbd-b37a-cbd00fef130c");});</script></div>

